verbose_text: Our finding that most mortality occurs in the coastal ocean hinges on our assumption that the detection probability of the Lippy Point sub-array, p LIP, was similar to other Pacific Ocean Shelf Tracking (POST) marine sub-arrays that could be directly assessed (too few smolts reached the final sub-array in Alaska, 1000 km distant, to allow direct estimation of p LIP; see Methods and XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY).
